_Hispa’el_ Future Tense for regular shorushim:
The [[_Hispa’el_ future tense]] follows the following conjugations for [[regular shorushim]]:
|| *Singular* |\<| *Plural* |\< |
| *First-Person* | אֲזַמֵּן<br>_azamein_<br>I will invite | \< | נְזַמֵּן<br>_nezamein_<br>We will invite | \< |
| *Second-Person* |תְּזַמֵּן <br>_tezamein_<br> You [male] will invite | תְּזַמְּנִי <br>_tezamni_<br> You [female] will invite  | תְּזַמְּנוּ <br>_tezamnu_<br> You [males] will invite  | תְּזַמֵּנָּה <br>_tezameinnau_<br> You [females] will invite  |
| *Third-Person* |יְזַמֵּן <br>_yezamein_<br> He will invite | תְּזַמֵּן <br>_tezamein_<br> She will invite  | יְזַמְּנוּ <br>_yezamnu_<br> [Those males] will invite  | תְּזַמֵּנָּה <br>_tezameinnau_<br> [Those females] will invite  |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ז, ‎מ, and ן above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
